<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880519-0070 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: GTE Unit Appoints Three to New Posts </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GTE WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   GTE Corp.'s GTE Telephone Operations unit named three to posts at its new information-systems business, which is to be headquartered in Tampa, Fla.    R.A. Cappellino, currently vice president, information management, at GTE Northwest, was named vice president, product management, at the information-systems operation.    Robert E. Stewart was appointed vice president, business development. He had been vice president, marketing, at GTE Florida.    Michael W. Yackira becomes vice president, finance and administration. He formerly was vice president, finance and revenues, at GTE Florida.    In March, GTE announced a restructuring of its telephone business to cut employment and centralize operations. </TEXT></DOC>